	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Yokosuka - The commander of the US Navy's 7th Fleet says that search and rescue efforts are over for the seven sailors missing after a destroyer collided with a merchant ship in waters off Japan. Vice Admiral Joseph Aucoin told reporters at a Navy base in Yokosuka, Japan, that a number of bodies have been recovered. He wouldn't say how many, pending notification of next of kin. The USS Fitzgerald sustained significant damage after a collision with a Philippine-flagged merchant ship on Saturday around 02:20. The bodies were found in flooded compartments Sunday after it returned to the base in Yokosuka with the help of tug boats. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  